  A1. Clay — Enrichment Waterfall Architecture
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  HIGH-LEVEL CONCEPT:
  Clay is not a data provider. It is an orchestration layer on top of 150+ data providers.
  You build sequential "waterfall" workflows: try Provider A, if no result try Provider B,
  then C. Stops the moment one returns data. Runs in a spreadsheet-like UI where each
  column is an enrichment step.

  IMPLEMENTATION DETAIL:

  What the waterfall config looks like:
  - A "Waterfall" column type in Clay's Airtable-like table UI
  - Drag-and-drop provider ordering within the waterfall
  - Toggle individual providers on/off with a switch
  - Set required inputs per step (email, LinkedIn URL, domain)
  - "Only run if" conditions to control when waterfall executes
  - Optional output column showing which provider succeeded (provenance)
  - Pre-built waterfall templates for common use cases (e.g., "Find Work Email")
  Evidence: https://university.clay.com/docs/building-a-data-waterfall

  Provider ecosystem (150+ integrations):
  - Email: Hunter.io (~1-2 credits), Apollo (~2), Prospeo (~2-3), Clearbit (~5-8),
    People Data Labs (~5), DropContact, Datagma, Nimbler, Lusha, Snov.io
  - Company/person: Clearbit, Apollo, PDL, ZoomInfo (BYOK only), Lusha (~8-15 for mobile)
  - Technographic: BuiltWith, Wappalyzer
  - Intent: Bombora, G2
  - AI/LLM: Claygent (Clay's own agent), OpenAI GPT-4, Anthropic Claude
  - BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) eliminates Data Credit costs, still 1 Action per enrichment
  Evidence: https://www.clay.com/integrations, https://mfishbein.com/clay-integrations/

  Conditional routing logic:
  - "Only run if" conditions on each step or entire waterfall
  - Operators: AND, OR, contains, equals, is empty, is not empty, >, <, regex
  - Example: {{email}} is empty — only run email waterfall if no email exists
  - Example: {{employee_count}} > 500 AND {{funding_round}} >= "Series B" — then enrich
    with Lusha for phone, else skip
  - Branch by geography: "If EU company, use DropContact first (GDPR). If US, use Hunter."
  - Disqualification columns: flag records, reference in conditions to skip entire waterfall
  Evidence: https://www.octavehq.com/post/clay-filters-conditions-enrichment-logic

  Credit economics (post-March 11, 2026 pricing overhaul):
  - Two metrics: Actions (1 per enrichment, no rollover) + Data Credits (0.5-10+ per
    provider, rollover up to 2x monthly limit)
  - Plans: Launch $185/mo (15K actions, 2.5-10K credits), Growth $495/mo (40K actions,
    6-100K credits), Enterprise custom (100K+)
  - Refund policy: "If a provider refunds us due to inability to deliver valid data, we
    correspondingly refund credits back to you" — but provider-dependent.
    Hunter.io on managed accounts charges ~2 credits regardless of result
  - Failed lookups consume 20-30% of credit allocation in practice
  - Fully enriched record (company + person + email + phone + AI): 6-20 Data Credits
    = ~$0.16/enriched lead at Pro tier
  - Emergency credit top-up: 30% surcharge
  Evidence: https://university.clay.com/docs/credits, https://www.clay.com/faq/what-happens-if-one-of-your-providers-doesnt-return-valid-data, https://hackceleration.com/clay-review/

  AI enrichment (Claygent):
  - Clay's LLM-based research agent, sits in waterfall or standalone
  - Receives natural-language prompt ("Find this company's SOC-2 compliance status")
  - Asks GPT-4 which section of website likely contains answer
  - Uses BINARY SEARCH approach: takes part of website, checks if data there, narrows
  - Model tiers: Helium (1 credit, simple), Neon (2), Argon (3), GPT-4/Claude (varies)
  - You can iterate on prompts in the builder WITHOUT spending credits
  - Best for unstructured "last-mile" insights (recent launches, hiring patterns, blog
    topics). Traditional APIs for structured data (email, phone, revenue, funding)
  Evidence: https://university.clay.com/lessons/enriching-with-claygent, https://www.clay.com/claygent, https://coldiq.com/blog/clay-ai-agent-claygent

  VERIFIED CASE STUDIES:

  OpenAI:
  - Before: single-source enrichment, coverage in "low 40%"
  - After: multi-provider waterfall, coverage in "high 80%" — more than 2x improvement
  - Refined provider combination and ordering within 2 weeks
  - 8,500+ enrichment runs by team members
  - Deployed as "Enrichment Actions" inside Salesforce (on-demand, no CRM exit)
  - Quote (Keith Jones, GTM Systems Lead): "Clay was a way to leapfrog us into a
