  A2. 6sense — Intent Scoring & Baseline Comparison
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  HIGH-LEVEL CONCEPT:
  6sense watches what companies are researching across the internet (via publisher data
  partnerships), compares activity against each company's historical baseline, and predicts
  which "buying stage" they're in. Separates "intent" (third-party research behavior)
  from "engagement" (first-party interaction with your brand).

  IMPLEMENTATION DETAIL:

  Intent score (0-100) — what feeds it:
  - Topic consumption volume relative to company's historical BASELINE
  - Recency weighting (more recent = higher score)
  - Content depth (pricing page > blog post)
  - Multi-signal correlation (web research + job postings + tech installs compound)
  - The score is an ML model output, NOT a simple linear formula
  - Exact weights are proprietary — 6sense has never published the formula
  Evidence: https://6sense.com/platform/intent-data/

  BASELINE COMPARISON mechanism (the critical concept):
  - Each account has a rolling ~16-week baseline activity window
  - "Intent" = statistically significant deviation from baseline (standard deviation
    thresholds, exact multiplier not published)
  - WITHOUT baseline comparison, you just measure how much a company uses the internet
  - A company that always reads industry news isn't showing intent; one that suddenly
    starts is
  - The baseline makes the score RELATIVE, not absolute
  Evidence: support.6sense.com support articles reference "baseline comparison" (exact
  article IDs vary), 6sense partner training materials

  Five buying stages — what triggers transitions:

  ┌──────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Stage        │ Trigger                                                   │
  ├──────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Target       │ Matches ICP firmographics, no intent above baseline       │
  │ Awareness    │ Mild increase on problem-space topics above baseline      │
  │ Consideration│ Solution-category keywords increase; multiple personas    │
  │              │ at account researching; competitor content detected        │
  │ Decision     │ High-intensity vendor-specific keywords, pricing/comparison│
  │              │ terms; activity concentrated in short windows             │
  │ Purchase     │ Strongest cluster: RFP terms, contract/procurement        │
  │              │ keywords, very high frequency direct vendor engagement    │
  └──────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Transition model: HIDDEN MARKOV MODEL (per 6sense engineering blog ~2023 and patent
  filings). Uses:
  - Volume of intent signals (absolute count)
  - Topic specificity (problem-level vs. solution-level vs. vendor-level keywords)
  - Velocity of change (how fast activity is increasing)
  - Breadth of research (number of distinct personas/IPs at the account)
  - No hard-coded thresholds. Probabilistic: assigns probability distribution across
    all 5 stages, reports most likely one
  - Reported ~80% accuracy validated against CRM opportunity creation data (self-reported,
    methodology not independently audited)
  Evidence: Patent US-20200364636-A1, https://6sense.com/blog/buying-stages/

  Intent score vs. Engagement score — exact distinction:
  - INTENT SCORE: third-party research behavior. What employees read across the open web
    via Bombora bidstream data, publisher co-ops, content syndication. Account does NOT
    need to visit your website. This is the "dark funnel"
  - ENGAGEMENT SCORE: first-party interactions with YOUR brand only. Website visits, email
    opens, ad clicks, webinar attendance, content downloads
  - Combined into "6QA" (6sense Qualified Account) = ready for sales handoff. Requires
    BOTH high intent AND meaningful engagement
  Evidence: https://6sense.com/blog/magic-numbers, https://support.6sense.com/hc/en-us/categories/

  Dark funnel / anonymous traffic matching:
  1. Reverse IP lookup (IP → company domain via ISP registration, table-stakes)
  2. Device graph correlation (TrustRadius acquisition + data co-ops link device IDs,
     cookies, MAIDs to company accounts)
  3. ML de-anonymization for VPNs/home offices: behavioral fingerprinting + LinkedIn/
     employer data for probabilistic company assignment. ~65% match rate claimed
  - Match accuracy varies significantly by segment (enterprise = higher, SMB = lower)
  Evidence: https://6sense.com/platform/company-identification/, Forrester Wave: B2B
  Intent Data Providers Q2 2023

  Verified customer results:
  - Thomson Reuters: 2x pipeline from 6sense-sourced accounts
    Evidence: https://6sense.com/customers/thomson-reuters/
  - Cognizant: 3x engagement rate increase with stage-based outreach
    Evidence: https://6sense.com/customers/cognizant/
  - PTC: 40% of pipeline from accounts identified before any inbound activity
    Evidence: 6sense Breakthrough 2023 keynote
  - Aggregate: 2.5x pipeline increase, 30% shorter sales cycles (self-reported survey)

  HONEST LIMITATIONS:
  - Strongest for enterprise B2B with 6+ month sales cycles
  - Dependent on Bombora's bidstream network (known gaps in some industries)
  - Pricing: ~$70K-$120K/year (per G2 reviews), firmly enterprise territory
  - For Civ Robotics: the EPC contractor segment may be too niche for 6sense's intent
    data to have meaningful coverage
  Evidence: G2 reviews (https://www.g2.com/products/6sense/reviews)

  KEY TAKEAWAY FOR OUR ARCHITECTURE:
  The baseline comparison concept is the gold. Our equivalent: track each EPC's typical
  project filing rate, and flag deviations. If Blattner typically files 2 projects/quarter
  and suddenly files 5, that's a surge. The fit vs. intent separation also maps directly
  to our lead scoring (fit = project size + EPC tier, intent = filing recency + timeline).

