  C. Additional Gaps Not in Main Summary
  ---

  C1. Gap 8 — Enrichment Waterfall with Provenance

  Current: Agent uses tools in whatever order Claude decides per-session. No consistent
  source ordering by reliability. No tracking of which source resolved which data point.

  What to build:
  - Define source priority order for EPC identification:
    1. Structured databases (SEC EDGAR filings naming the contractor)
    2. Official press releases (developer or EPC announcing the contract)
    3. Industry rankings (Wiki-Solar, SPW, ENR — confirms company is an EPC)
    4. Government records (OSHA — indirect, confirms presence not contract)
    5. News articles (varying quality, check recency)
    6. General web search (lowest signal, highest noise)
  - Track provenance per data point: {value, source, url, confidence, retrieved_at}
  - When waterfall exhausts: mark as "unresolved" with sources attempted. Schedule
    re-enrichment in 2 weeks. Never report "unknown" without saying what was tried

  C2. Gap 9 — No Sales Pipeline Closure Loop

  Current: HubSpot push creates company + deal + contacts. One-way. No outcome tracking.

  What to build (future):
  - Bi-directional HubSpot sync: pull deal stage changes back into KB
  - Track funnel: discovery → CRM → contacted → responded → meeting → opportunity → closed
  - Use conversion data to improve lead scoring
  - Per-EPC relationship status: "Blattner — 3 deals pushed, 1 meeting, 0 closed"

  Why it matters: Without closure loop, you can't improve. After 6 months you should be
  able to say "discoveries with lead score >80 convert at 12%, <40 convert at 0.5%"

  C3. Gap 10 — No Project Versioning

  Current: If EPC changes post-announcement, old discovery gets overwritten. Pending
  discoveries block re-research. No multi-phase support.

  What to build:
  - Discovery versioning: new EPC found → mark old as "superseded" not replaced
  - Multi-phase support: epc_engagements.phase field for multiple EPCs per project
  - Auto-expire old pending discoveries after N days without review
  - Change detection: re-research finds different EPC → flag as conflict

